1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact sections 27-02.2-01, 27-02.2-02, 27-02.2-03,
2 27-02.2-04, 27-02.2-05, 27-02.2-06, 27-02.2-09, 27-02.2-10, and 27-02.2-11 of the North
3 Dakota Century Code, relating to the attorney recruitment and retention program.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
5 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 27-02.2-01 of the North Dakota Century Code is
6 amended and reenacted as follows:
7 27-02.2-01. Attorney recruitment and retention program - Participation - Assessment.
8 1. The supreme court may establish a program to assist rural counties and municipalities
9 in recruiting and retaining attorneys.
10 2. A county or municipality interested in participating in the program shall apply to the
11 supreme court. After determining eligibility, the supreme court shall conduct an
12 assessment of the applicant to evaluate the applicant's need for an attorney and the
13 ability of the applicant to sustain and support an attorney.
14 3. In making the selection of an eligible applicant, the supreme court shall consider the
15 assessment and:
16 a. The demographic of the county or municipality;
17 b. The age and number of the members of the county or local bar association;
18 c. The recommendation of the presiding district court judge;
19 d. The economic development programs within the county or municipality;
20 e. The geographical location of the county or municipality in comparison to other
21 counties or municipalities participating in the program; and
22 f. Any prior participation in the program by the county or municipality.
