1 4. The supreme court shall maintain a list of counties and municipalities that have been
2 assessed and are selected for participation in the recruitment and retention assistance
3 program.
4 5. The supreme court may revise the assessment of any county or municipality or
5 conduct a new assessment as necessary to reflect a change in conditions.
6 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Section 27-02.2-02 of the North Dakota Century Code is
7 amended and reenacted as follows:
8 27-02.2-02. County eligibility.
9 A county is eligible to participate in the recruitment and retention assistance program if the
10 county:
11 1. Has a population of sixteen thousandfive or fewer licensed attorneys residing in the
12 county;
13 2. Agrees to provide the county's portion of the incentive payment as required under
14 section 27-02.2-06; and
15 3. Is determined to be eligible by the supreme court.
16 SECTION 3. AMENDMENT. Section 27-02.2-03 of the North Dakota Century Code is
17 amended and reenacted as follows:
18 27-02.2-03. Municipality eligibility.
19 A municipality is eligible to participate in the recruitment and retention assistance program if
20 the municipality:
21 1. Has a population of five thousand or fewer;
22 2. Agrees to provide the municipality's portion of the incentive payment as required under
23 section 27-02.2-06; and
24 3. Is determined to be eligible by the supreme court.
25 SECTION 4. AMENDMENT. Section 27-02.2-04 of the North Dakota Century Code is
26 amended and reenacted as follows:
27 27-02.2-04. Attorney eligibility.
28 An attorney licensed to practice in the state who meets all requirements set by the supreme
29 court may participate in the recruitment and retention assistance program. An attorney
30 participating in the program shall practice in a supreme court-selected county or municipality for
