1 at least five consecutive years. No more than eight attorneys may participate in the program at
2 any given time.
3 SECTION 5. AMENDMENT. Section 27-02.2-05 of the North Dakota Century Code is
4 amended and reenacted as follows:
5 27-02.2-05. Incentive payment to participating attorneys.
6 An attorney selected by the supreme court to participate in the recruitment and retention
7 assistance program is entitled to receive an incentive payment of forty-five thousand dollars to
8 be paid in five equal annual installments.
9 SECTION 6. AMENDMENT. Section 27-02.2-06 of the North Dakota Century Code is
10 amended and reenacted as follows:
11 27-02.2-06. Agreement for payment of recruitment and retention assistance -
12 Repayment.
13 1. An agreement for the payment of recruitment and retention assistance under this
14 chapter must require the county or municipality served by the attorney to provide
15 thirty-five percent of the total amount of the incentive payment in five equal
16 installments.
17 2. The state bar association of North Dakota, the North Dakota bar foundation, or any
18 other legal association in North Dakota shall pay fifteen percent of the annual
19 installment to the supreme court.
20 3. After the county or municipality certifies to the supreme court that the county or
21 municipality has paid the attorney the annual amount and the state bar association of
22 North Dakota, the North Dakota bar foundation, or any other legal association in North
23 Dakota has paid its installment to the supreme court, the supreme court shall pay the
24 attorney the remaining balance of the annual installment.
25 4. Subject to appropriation by the legislative assembly, the supreme court shall pay the
26 required amount of funds pursuant to this chapter and the funds received from the
27 state bar association of North Dakota, the North Dakota bar foundation, or any other
28 legal association in North Dakota, as required under this chapter, to an attorney
29 participating in the program.
