1 5. If an attorney breaches the agreement, the attorney shall repay all funds received
2 under this chapter and under the terms and conditions set by the supreme court.
3 Failure to repay the funds is grounds for discipline by the supreme court.
4 SECTION 7. AMENDMENT. Section 27-02.2-09 of the North Dakota Century Code is
5 amended and reenacted as follows:
6 27-02.2-09. Attorney recruitment and retention assistance program fund - Continuing
7 appropriation.
8 The attorney recruitment and retention assistance program fund is established in the state
9 treasury. Payments collected under section 27-02.2-08 must be deposited in the attorney
10 recruitment and retention assistance program fund. The funds deposited in the attorney
11 recruitment and retention assistance program fund are appropriated to the judicial branch on a
12 continuing basis for the purpose of making attorney payments under the recruitment and
13 retention assistance program.
14 SECTION 8. AMENDMENT. Section 27-02.2-10 of the North Dakota Century Code is
15 amended and reenacted as follows:
16 27-02.2-10. Filing and approval of recruitment and retention assistance agreement.
17 A recruitment and retention assistance agreement entered under this chapter becomes
18 effective when the agreement is filed with and approved by the supreme court. The agreement
19 must require the attorney to practice law full-time in the eligible county or municipality for at
20 least five consecutive years.
21 SECTION 9. AMENDMENT. Section 27-02.2-11 of the North Dakota Century Code is
22 amended and reenacted as follows:
23 27-02.2-11. Ineligibility for participation in other program.
24 If an individual has previously participated in an attorney recruitment and retention program
25 under this chapter, or any other state or federal scholarship, loan repayment, or tuition
26 reimbursement program requiring the individual to provide attorney services within an
27 underserved area, the individual may not participate in another attorney recruitment and
28 retention program under this chapter.
